## **Description**
The **Tokenize **operator allows to split an input string into multiple outputs, returned as substrings (tokens) using one of the two accepted criteria:

- specifying a fixed length for every token

- specifying a character (or a sequence of characters) as delimiter

## **Input**
**Input**

**Data type**

**Description**

**in0**

String

The string containing a series of values, separated by a character separator, from which you want to extract a series of tokens or substrings.

## **Output**
**Output**

**Data type**

**Description**

**out1, ..., out*n***

String list

A series of strings containing the *n *tokens returned from the operator.

## **Settings**
**![](data:image/png;base64,)**

- In the **Output **section, click  ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Add**) to add an output node to the list.

> Note

You may add a minimum of 1 and a maximum of 50 output nodes.

- In the **Token **section, select the split mode:

**Use delimiter**: Select a delimiter from the list, or enter a custom delimiter in the text box. It is also possible to use a convention to identify hexadecimal characters.

- **Use fixed length**: Set the length of each token/output returned.

> Tip

To rename an output node, click on its name to edit it.

To remove an output node from the list, move your mouse over it and click ![](data:image/png;base64,) in the **Action **column; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

## **Special cases**
In special cases, the operator behaves as follows:

**Case**

**Behavior**

***n *tokens**

***m *outputs**

***n *&lt; *m***

The operator sends the ***n ***tokens in the first ***n ***output connectors while the (***m ****- ****n***) outputs will be NULL and a warning message will be displayed in the console.

***n *tokens**

***m *outputs**

***n *&gt; *m***

The operator only sends the first ***m ***tokens in their respective output connectors. The remaining (***n ****- ****m***) tokens will be discarded and a warning message will be displayed in the message console.

***n *length last token j**

***i *fixed length output *j***

***n *&lt; *i***

The output connector will return a string of length ***n ***and a warning message will be displayed in the message console.

**delimiter = ""**

An error during validation is returned if an empty string is selected by using the delimiter criteria, and a message with the text "There arent delimiter in the functor" is shown inside the message console.
